<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idd394c8fc-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370" identifier="/us/usc/t11/s750"><num value="750">§ 750.</num><heading> Distribution of securities</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The trustee may not distribute a security except under <ref href="/us/usc/t11/s751">section 751 of this title</ref>.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idd394c8fd-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370">(<ref href="/us/pl/95/598">Pub. L. 95–598</ref>, <date date="1978-11-06">Nov. 6, 1978</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/92/2614">92 Stat. 2614</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idd394c8fe-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="idd394c8ff-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="miscellaneous" id="idd394c900-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370"><heading class="centered smallCaps">senate report no. 95–989</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section 750 forbids the trustee from distributing a security other than a customer name security. The term “distribution” refers to a distribution to customers in satisfaction of net equity claims and is not intended to preclude the trustee from liquidating securities under proposed <ref href="/us/usc/t11/s748">11 U.S.C. 748</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
